{"title":"MMR Adrenaline Aero brings more speed, stability and style to their latest aero road bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/mmr-adrenaline-aero-brings-more-speed-stability-and-style-to-their-latest-aero-road-bike/","date":1639067130000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06162021/Adrenaline-Aero-Action-2.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"530\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06162021/Adrenaline-Aero-Action-2-800x530.jpg\" alt=\"MMR Adrenaline Aero in motion. Front side view.\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06162021/Adrenaline-Aero-Action-2-800x530.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06162021/Adrenaline-Aero-Action-2-297x197.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06162021/Adrenaline-Aero-Action-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06162021/Adrenaline-Aero-Action-2-768x509.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06162021/Adrenaline-Aero-Action-2-1536x1018.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06162021/Adrenaline-Aero-Action-2-2048x1358.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-280171\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>‘Tis the season for new bikes from MMR. It’s been a busy year for the folks behind the Spanish bicycle company with a penchant for making high-end race bikes.</p><div id=\"attachment_280174\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280174\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160335/MMR-Adrenaline-side-1-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"MMR Adrenaline Aero full side view.\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1704\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160335/MMR-Adrenaline-side-1-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160335/MMR-Adrenaline-side-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160335/MMR-Adrenaline-side-1-800x532.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160335/MMR-Adrenaline-side-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160335/MMR-Adrenaline-side-1-768x511.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160335/MMR-Adrenaline-side-1-1536x1022.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160335/MMR-Adrenaline-side-1-2048x1363.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280174\">MMR has released the fourth generation of its Adrenaline Aero bike.</p></div><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/mmr-kenta-xc-bike-finally-hits-the-trails-following-world-cup-olympic-refinement/\">Hot off the release of the latest Kenta XC mountain bike range</a>, MMR has dropped yet another new offering. This time, MMR stuck to the pavement to design the latest edition of the Adrenaline Aero range—a super-fast, aerodynamic option the company says is stiffer, more stable, and better looking than its three previous renditions.</p><div id=\"attachment_280176\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280176\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160355/MMR-rear-detail-1-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"MMR Adrenaline Aero rear frame details view.\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1704\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160355/MMR-rear-detail-1-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160355/MMR-rear-detail-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160355/MMR-rear-detail-1-800x532.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160355/MMR-rear-detail-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160355/MMR-rear-detail-1-768x511.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160355/MMR-rear-detail-1-1536x1022.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160355/MMR-rear-detail-1-2048x1363.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280176\">MMR has added aerodynamic integrations to the new Adrenaline Aero range to increase speed and stability.</p></div><p>In the same vein as the redesigned Kenta range, which was honed to its final form after a year of World Cup and Olympic competition, the Adrenaline Aero is the product of a collaboration between the company and the Caja Rural-Seguros RGA Team.</p><div id=\"attachment_280175\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280175\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160346/mmr-aero-side-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"MMR Adrenaline Aero side view phot taken outdoors from a distance.\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1704\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160346/mmr-aero-side-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160346/mmr-aero-side-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160346/mmr-aero-side-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160346/mmr-aero-side-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160346/mmr-aero-side-768x511.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160346/mmr-aero-side-1536x1022.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160346/mmr-aero-side-2048x1363.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280175\">MMR is offering the Adrenaline Aero in five builds ranging from a little more than $3,000 to more than $6,000.</p></div><p>MMR says the bike is built to race at the highest levels of competition, with a keen focus on geometry and integration between the frame, cables, stem, fork, and seat post to maximize aerodynamics. It is expected to run in races alongside the lightweight Adrenaline SL.</p><p>MMR is offering the new models in five different builds: the 00, 10, 30, 50, or 70, which range in price from about &nbsp;MSRP $3,160 to $6,320.</p><div id=\"attachment_280173\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280173\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160330/MMR-Adrenaline-rear-detail-1-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"MMR Adrenaline Aero rear tire clearance detail view.\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160330/MMR-Adrenaline-rear-detail-1-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160330/MMR-Adrenaline-rear-detail-1-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160330/MMR-Adrenaline-rear-detail-1-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160330/MMR-Adrenaline-rear-detail-1-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160330/MMR-Adrenaline-rear-detail-1-768x576.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160330/MMR-Adrenaline-rear-detail-1-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06160330/MMR-Adrenaline-rear-detail-1-2048x1536.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280173\">The MMR Adrenaline Aero has enough tire clearance to accommodate a 28mm tire.</p></div><p>The 00 comes equipped with SRAM Force AXS 12v and DT Swiss ARC 1400 Carbo 50 wheels. The 10 features the Shimano Ultra Di2 12v and DT Swiss ARC 1400 Carbon 50 wheels. The 30 includes the Shimano Rival 12v and Vision SC-40 Carbon wheels. The 50 comes with the Shimano Ultegra 11v &nbsp;and Vision SC-40 Carbon wheels. Finally, the 70 includes the Shimano 105 11v and DT Swiss P1800 S wheels.</p><div id=\"attachment_280179\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280179\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06162016/Adrenaline-Aero-action-1.jpg\" alt=\"Man riding 2022 MMR Adrenaline Aero. Front view.\" width=\"2150\" height=\"1430\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06162016/Adrenaline-Aero-action-1.jpg 2150w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06162016/Adrenaline-Aero-action-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06162016/Adrenaline-Aero-action-1-800x532.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06162016/Adrenaline-Aero-action-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06162016/Adrenaline-Aero-action-1-768x511.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06162016/Adrenaline-Aero-action-1-1536x1022.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06162016/Adrenaline-Aero-action-1-2048x1362.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2150px) 100vw, 2150px\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280179\">The 2022 MMR Adrenaline Aero is expected to join the race line up alongside MMR’s existing Adrenaline SL.</p></div><p>The 00 build is only available in Chrome Red. All other models come in Chrome Red or Carbon “N” White.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.mmrbikes.com/\">MMRbikes.com</a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Mark Wilson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"13e2fa3ef192eb1c598639f9c43cd04d28eab1a6ae9cabf6164cac4400c0bd99","category":"Cycling"}